Now you might be wondering what kind of uses there are for plastic string, and the answer is probably as many uses as there are for normal string.

00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:09.040
You can use it as improvised fishing line, you can use to rig a snare or hold up your tent when you're out in the woods.

00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:13.340
or if you're using something like my rope-making machine, you might be able to wind it into an actual length of rope.

00:04:14.060 --> 00:04:19.540
Now there really are so many ways that you can approach this guys.  You can use kitchen knives, you can use hunting knives, you can use wooding knives.

00:04:19.540 --> 00:04:23.560
You can even use razor blades out of your utility knife and shove that up in there as well.

00:04:23.560 --> 00:04:30.420
As for as the thickness of the rope goes, your can make anything, almost as thin as fishing line, to about as thick of any cable as you'd want to make.

00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:33.900
And for as thin as this chord is, it really is pretty strong stuff.

00:04:34.540 --> 00:04:35.820
Of course you can break it.

00:04:35.820 --> 00:04:37.260
But the thicker you go.....

00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:40.220
The much more difficult it is to break.

